Notes for Creating New language files and dealing with language issues.

The current translation system in phpBB is not perfect. Some errors and/or 
discrepancies are bound to exist. Each language file has been done by 
someone different so if you find any errors please report them to 
bugs@phpbb.com, it would also be preferable if you submitted a fix along 
with the report.

To create a new language for your forums is a very simple operation. Open up
one of the other language files that you can read and understand and simply
translate all of the strings with in the file. For example:

$l_username = "Username";

in english would become:

$l_username = "Nom d'Utilisateur";

in French and so on. If you find any string that have variables in them (any
text starting with a $) DO NOT translate the variable name! For example

In english:
$l_noposts  = "No $l_posts";

Would become:
$l_noposts  = "Pas de $l_posts";
in the french languge file.

Once the file is done, save it as lang_<language>.<your phpBB extention> in
the languages dir under you phpBB dir.

For example if you create a language file for Japanese, and your forum uses
the .php3 extention you would save it as:

lang_japanese.php3

Also, the FAQ has not been translated. In order to get phpBB version 1.2 out 
in a timely manner we did not have time to create separate FAQ's. However, 
we did put a very simple system in place for you to add new FAQ's in 
different languages to your forum. To add a new FAQ in a language currently 
in use on your forum simple drop a file called faq-<your forums default 
language>.<your forums file extension> into your phpBB dir.

For example, if you are using the German language on your forum and you use 
the .php extension you would add a faq of this name:

faq-german.php

If you are using Big5 Chinese and you are using .html extensions you would 
drop a in file named like this:

faq-big5_chinese.html

This also works for Translated images. For example if you are using German 
on your forum and you want someone who selects English to see a different, 
English, header image you would drop a file into the images dir like this:

header_image-german.jpg

Based on what your header image is called in the current theme.

This all probably sounds pretty complicated but we are always available to 
help at http://www.phpbb.com/phpBB

If you create a new language file, or a FAQ translation we would ask that
you send it to use so we can post it on phpBB.com for others to download.

Thanks,

The phpBB Group
